# 2. High-level architecture

```text
Rust exact state
  -> full start-of-turn LEGAL rows
  -> Rust tactical payload
  -> Python graph/set encoder
  -> per-LEGAL hidden states H_i
  -> cell marginal logits M_i
  -> low-rank pair embeddings Q_i, K_i
  -> dense queryable pair surface L(i,j)
  -> candidate_selector_lowrank_v1
  -> bounded candidate reservoir with metadata
  -> optional admitted-candidate residual rerank
  -> Rust sampled pair MCTS
  -> root improved candidate-conditional target
  -> replay
  -> candidate-aware training losses
```

The model should expose a dense pair-prior API, but search should still operate on a bounded reservoir:

```text
C(s) subset of all legal unordered pairs
```

The central target object is:

[
\pi^*_C(a \mid s), \quad a \in C(s)
]

not:

[
\pi^*(a \mid s), \quad a \in \mathcal A(s)
]

unless the pair set is exhaustive.

