# 3. Model spec: `global_pair_lowrank_0`

## 3.1 Input objects

The graph/set encoder consumes the same logical object families as V1:

```text
STATE
TURN
STONE
LEGAL
WINDOW6
```

### STATE object

One per position.

Required features:

```text
current_player
ply_index
turn_index
phase
num_stones_player_0
num_stones_player_1
legal_row_count
active_window_count
terminal_status
```

Optional but recommended:

```text
last_move_age_summary
board_span_q
board_span_r
board_span_s
root_player_if_search_context
```

### TURN object

One per current turn.

Required features:

```text
current_player
placements_remaining
is_opening_single
is_normal_two_placement
is_terminal
```

For normal Hexo after opening:

```text
placements_remaining = 2
```

### STONE objects

One per occupied cell.

Required features:

```text
axial_q
axial_r
owner_player
relative_to_current_player
move_age_bucket
distance_to_last_move_bucket
```

Recommended positional features:

```text
cube_s = -q-r
relative_q_centered
relative_r_centered
relative_s_centered
D6 transform id during augmentation
```

### LEGAL objects

One per full Rust-legal placement row.

Required features:

```text
legal_row_id
axial_q
axial_r
cube_s
distance_to_nearest_stone_bucket
distance_to_last_move_bucket
is_center
phase_flags
```

Tactical support features may be attached, but must be interpreted as labels/proposal support, not as legal filters:

```text
is_own_winning_single_cell
is_opponent_required_cover_cell
num_own_hot_windows_touched
num_opponent_hot_windows_touched
```

### WINDOW6 objects

One per active 6-cell line window.

Required features:

```text
axis_id
owner_0_count
owner_1_count
empty_count
current_player_count
opponent_count
is_dead
is_current_player_5_window
is_current_player_4_window
is_opponent_5_window
is_opponent_4_window
```

Window objects are important because Hexo strategy is dominated by hot windows, immediate completions, covers, and stacked threats. 

## 3.2 Required relations

The encoder must support at least these sparse relations:

```text
STONE -> WINDOW6
LEGAL -> WINDOW6
WINDOW6 -> LEGAL
WINDOW6 -> WINDOW6 overlap
LEGAL -> nearby LEGAL offset bucket
LEGAL -> nearby STONE proximity bucket
LEGAL -> same-axis LEGAL
LEGAL -> same-line LEGAL
```

The model must not create full pair tokens for all legal pairs.

Allowed:

```text
LEGAL-to-LEGAL sparse local relations
LEGAL-to-WINDOW relations
blockwise pair score computation outside attention
candidate-only pair residual MLP
```

Forbidden for mainline:

```text
all legal pairs as graph tokens
O(N^2) pair-token attention
legal-order first-N pair generation
threat-filtered LEGAL rows
```

