# 4. Encoder

## 4.1 Recommended encoder shape

Default implementation:

```text
d_model = 256
num_layers = 6
num_attention_heads = 8
ffn_dim = 1024
dropout = 0.0 to 0.1
activation = SiLU or GELU
normalization = pre-LayerNorm
```

The encoder can be implemented as either:

```text
sparse graph transformer
heterogeneous message-passing network
set transformer with relation biases
```

Minimum requirement:

```text
input LEGAL rows -> output H_legal[N, d_model]
input STATE/TURN/WINDOW/STONE context -> global state embedding G[d_model]
```

Outputs:

```text
H_legal: float[N, d_model]
G_state: float[d_model]
H_window: optional float[W, d_model]
```

## 4.2 Global pooling

The global state vector should be built from:

```text
STATE token hidden state
TURN token hidden state
attention-pool over LEGAL rows
attention-pool over active WINDOW6 rows
attention-pool over recent STONE rows
```

Recommended:

[
G =
\operatorname{MLP}
(
h_{\text{STATE}},
h_{\text{TURN}},
\operatorname{AttnPool}(H_{\text{LEGAL}}),
\operatorname{AttnPool}(H_{\text{WINDOW}})
)
]

