# 6. Runtime pair-scoring API

The model/provider must expose these operations.

## 6.1 Score specific pairs

```python
score_pairs(
    legal_hidden: Tensor[N, d_model],
    cell_marginal_logits: Tensor[N],
    q: Tensor[N, d_pair_rank],
    k: Tensor[N, d_pair_rank],
    pair_indices: Tensor[K, 2],
    cheap_pair_features: Tensor[K, f_cheap],
    full_pair_features: Optional[Tensor[K, f_full]],
    use_residual: bool,
) -> Tensor[K]
```

Returns:

```text
pair_logits[K]
```

Must enforce:

```text
i != j
canonical pair key
finite logits
same legal row table hash
```

## 6.2 Compute blockwise top-k pairs

```python
topk_pairs_blockwise(
    M: Tensor[N],
    Q: Tensor[N, d],
    K: Tensor[N, d],
    legal_rows,
    k_total: int,
    block_size: int,
    masks,
    cheap_feature_provider,
) -> list[PairCandidate]
```

Algorithm:

```text
global_heap = empty min-heap of size k_total

for block_a in legal rows:
  for block_b in legal rows:
    compute L_block for pairs in block_a x block_b
    mask diagonal
    mask lower triangle if same block
    mask illegal / forbidden
    local_topk = top k_block from L_block
    merge local_topk into global_heap

return heap sorted by descending score
```

Requirements:

```text
exact for configured candidate pool
D6-stable
row-order-stable
diagonal-masked
deduplicated by canonical pair key
chunking-stable
```

For small (N), the implementation may compute the full matrix:

[
L = M\mathbf{1}^{T}+\mathbf{1}M^T+\frac{QK^T+KQ^T}{2\sqrt{d}}
]

then mask and top-k the upper triangle.

## 6.3 Full matrix mode

Full matrix construction is allowed only for:

```text
small-state exhaustive audit
debugging
tiny-state training experiments
candidate retrieval when N is below threshold
```

It should not be required by MCTS.

Configuration:

```text
full_matrix_threshold_N = 256   # tune by hardware
block_size = 256 or 512
```

