# 7. Candidate selector: `candidate_selector_lowrank_v1`

## 7.1 Candidate sources

The selector must combine sources by quota, not by one blended sampler.

| Source                          |    Required | Purpose                                                         |
| ------------------------------- | ----------: | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `terminal_exact_v1`             |         yes | Own hot completions, opponent covers, terminal-equivalent pairs |
| `lowrank_direct_topk`           |         yes | Main learned relational pair source                             |
| `cell_marginal_cross`           |         yes | Dense unary baseline and stability source                       |
| `anchor_conditioned_completion` | recommended | Autoregressive-style recovery source                            |
| `structured_diversity`          |         yes | Prevent low-rank/top-k support collapse                         |
| `blind_canary`                  |   yes, tiny | Diagnostic recall/collapse probe                                |
| `manual_audit_pairs`            |       debug | Deterministic tests and oracle fixtures                         |

The V1 proposal already requires multiple candidate sources, tactical protection, direct pair retrieval, structured exploration, and diagnostic canaries. This spec makes low-rank direct retrieval the main learned pair source. 

## 7.2 Default quotas

Root defaults:

```text
root_total_candidate_budget = 1024

terminal_exact_v1: protected, no ordinary eviction
lowrank_direct_topk: 512
cell_marginal_cross: 128
anchor_conditioned_completion: 128
structured_diversity: 192
blind_canary: 16
reserve / overflow: 48
```

Interior defaults:

```text
interior_total_candidate_budget = 256

terminal_exact_v1: protected
lowrank_direct_topk: 128
cell_marginal_cross: 32
anchor_conditioned_completion: 32
structured_diversity: 48
blind_canary: 4
reserve / overflow: 14
```

These are starting values. Tune by:

```text
candidate recall
missed-pair regret
pair target entropy
wall-clock throughput
```

