# 8. Python expansion provider

## 8.1 One-pass node expansion

This low-rank spec should avoid the current two-full-pass lifecycle. The current V1 implementation does a proposal pass without pair rows, then constructs admitted pair rows and runs a final pair-scoring graph pass. 

New lifecycle:

```text
1. Rust sends expansion request.
2. Python builds graph with STATE/TURN/STONE/LEGAL/WINDOW6 rows.
3. Model runs one encoder pass.
4. Model emits value, M, Q, K, optional tactical heads.
5. Python computes low-rank candidate scores from cached per-LEGAL outputs.
6. Candidate selector builds bounded reservoir.
7. Optional residual MLP scores admitted candidate pairs only.
8. Python returns candidate records, final logits, and value to Rust.
```

There must be no second full graph encoder pass.

Allowed:

```text
one lightweight candidate-only residual pass
one blockwise matmul retrieval pass
one pair-feature construction pass
```

Forbidden:

```text
full graph re-encode with admitted pair rows
per-pair model calls
per-widening model calls
per-second-placement model calls
```

## 8.2 Batched expansion

Python must batch expansion requests.

Recommended provider loop:

```python
requests = rust_engine.run_search_step(max_expansions=batch_size)

graphs = [build_graph(req) for req in requests]
batch = collate_graphs(graphs)

model_outputs = model(batch)

for req, out in zip(requests, unbatch(model_outputs)):
    candidates = candidate_selector_lowrank_v1(req, out)
    response = build_expansion_response(req, out.value, candidates)
    rust_engine.complete_expansion(response)
```

Provider metrics:

```text
encoder_forward_count
encoder_forward_latency_p50_p95
blockwise_topk_latency_p50_p95
candidate_build_latency_p50_p95
residual_scoring_latency_p50_p95
expanded_nodes_per_second
pair_scores_per_second
```

