# 11. Training target builder

## 11.1 Main pair-policy loss

For a replay state with target support (S):

[
L_{\text{pair}}
===============

-\sum_{a \in S}
\pi^**S(a)
\log
\frac{
\exp L*\theta(a)
}{
\sum_{b \in S}\exp L_\theta(b)
}
]

Important:

```text
denominator = target support S
not all legal pairs
not all model-queryable pairs
not unadmitted pairs
```

Only use full legal-pair denominator if:

```text
support_type = exhaustive_legal_pair_table
```

## 11.2 Low-rank dense auxiliary loss

Allowed in tiny exhaustive states:

[
L_{\text{full-pair}}
====================

-\sum_{a \in \mathcal A(s)}
\pi^*(a)
\log
\operatorname{softmax}*{b \in \mathcal A(s)}
L*\theta(b)
]

Allowed in normal self-play only if explicit negative support is valid:

```text
admitted searched weak candidates
explicit sampled negatives with valid proposal semantics
oracle-known dominated pairs
```

Do not use random unsearched pairs as negatives by default.

## 11.3 Cell marginal projection loss

From pair target:

[
\pi_{\text{cell}}(i)
====================

\sum_{j:{i,j}\in S}
\pi^*_S({i,j})
]

Train:

[
L_{\text{cell}}
===============

\operatorname{CE}
(
\operatorname{softmax}(M_i \text{ over legal cells}),
\pi_{\text{cell}}
)
]

Coverage gating:

```text
only full weight if pair support around cell i is adequate
downweight if S is narrow or source-biased
```

Store:

```text
per_cell_support_count
per_cell_pair_mass
coverage_weight
```

## 11.4 Conditional completion loss

For meaningful anchors:

[
\pi(j|i)
========

\frac{\pi^*_S({i,j})}
{\sum_k \pi^*_S({i,k})}
]

Train both orientations:

```text
p(second = j | first = i)
p(second = i | first = j)
```

Do not train only canonical first-row order.

## 11.5 Value loss

Use game outcome (z) from current-player perspective at the stored state:

[
L_{\text{value}} = (v_\theta(s)-z)^2
]

Optional:

```text
Huber loss
value calibration bins by phase
```

## 11.6 Tactical losses

Use Rust tactical payload labels:

```text
own_winning_single_cell
own_hot_completion_pair
terminal_equivalent_pair
opponent_required_cover_cell
cover_all_opponent_win_requirements_pair
impossible_to_cover_state
```

Suggested losses:

```text
binary cross entropy for cells
candidate-conditional BCE for tactical pair rows
scalar BCE for impossible_to_cover
```

The tactical labels come from Rust, not from candidate masks.

## 11.7 Terminal-equivalence rule

If a state has a single winning cell and many equivalent filler choices:

```text
do not train arbitrary pair filler preference
```

Allowed target treatments:

```text
1. Omit pair-policy loss for filler distinctions.
2. Collapse all pairs containing winning_cell into one equivalence class.
3. Train cell/tactical heads strongly on winning_cell.
```

This is essential because Hexo’s 5-window threat is won by one placement and the second placement is irrelevant filler. 

## 11.8 Total loss

Recommended initial loss:

[
L =
\lambda_{\text{pair}}L_{\text{pair}}
+
\lambda_{\text{cell}}L_{\text{cell}}
+
\lambda_{\text{cond}}L_{\text{cond}}
+
\lambda_{\text{value}}L_{\text{value}}
+
\lambda_{\text{tactical}}L_{\text{tactical}}
+
\lambda_{\text{reg}}L_{\text{reg}}
]

Initial weights:

```text
lambda_pair = 1.0
lambda_cell = 0.25
lambda_cond = 0.25
lambda_value = 1.0
lambda_tactical = 0.5
lambda_reg = 0.01
```

Regularizers:

```text
pair logit L2
dot_component variance monitor
entropy floor during bootstrap
D6 consistency loss
marginal/dot balance penalty if one component dominates
```

