# 12. Numerical implementation details

## 12.1 Dot-product scaling

Use:

[
\frac{Q_i^\top K_j}{\sqrt{d_r}}
]

or normalize embeddings:

```text
Q_norm = Q / max(eps, ||Q||)
K_norm = K / max(eps, ||K||)
dot = scale * Q_norm @ K_norm.T
```

Default recommendation:

```text
scaled unnormalized dot with LayerNorm before Q/K projections
```

## 12.2 Logit clipping

Before softmax in search:

```text
clip logits to [-30, 30]
```

For training:

```text
do not hard clip unless necessary
use stable log_softmax
```

## 12.3 Precision

Recommended:

```text
encoder: bf16 or fp16 allowed
QK matmul: fp32 accumulation preferred
top-k scores: fp32
Rust priors/Q: f32
```

## 12.4 Component telemetry

For every candidate, log:

```text
marginal_component
dot_component
cheap_feature_component
residual_component
final_logit
```

Track:

```text
std(marginal_component)
std(dot_component)
std(residual_component)
correlation(final_logit, marginal_component)
correlation(final_logit, dot_component)
```

This catches collapse into “top marginal + top marginal.”

---

# 13. D6 symmetry

Hex grid augmentation must support 12 D6 transforms. Axis-related features and targets must be reindexed under rotations/reflections because the three hex axes permute. 

Required tests:

```text
legal row identity maps correctly under D6
pair key maps correctly under D6
L(i,j) transformed == L(T(i), T(j)) within tolerance
value transformed == value within tolerance
cell marginal target transforms correctly
pair target transforms correctly
window axis labels transform correctly
```

D6 consistency loss:

[
L_{\text{D6}}
=============

\operatorname{KL}
(
\pi_\theta(T(s)),
T(\pi_\theta(s))
)
+
(v_\theta(T(s))-v_\theta(s))^2
]

Use candidate support intersection when candidate sets differ.

---

# 14. Start-of-turn legality test

This spec requires a Rust property test:

```text
For every normal two-placement state s:
  for every legal first cell i in start_legal(s):
      second_legal_after_applying_i
      must equal start_legal(s) - {i}
```

If this fails under the actual game rules, unordered start-of-turn pair MCTS is not semantically valid.

